tists who would follow, but for the critics who celebrated them as well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aPainting, French. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  amodernism, modernity, robert delaunay, orphism, orphic cubism, pure abstraction, bright colors, fauvism, abstract art, geometric shapes, sonia, experimentation, history, historical, paris, france, french, paintings, creativity, artwork, vision, spiritual motivations, idealism, optics, visualization, windows, painting, divisionism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226159232423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226159232/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles